communication-tutorial-name = Communication and radio
communication-tutorial-tooltip = Learn to use local chat, whispering, emotes, LOOC, radio, and messenger.

comm-tut-local-chat-bubble = Write a short phrase in local chat. For example: "Hello".
comm-tut-local-chat-chat = First, let's check normal speech. Local chat is only heard by people standing near you.
comm-tut-local-chat-tts = First, let's check normal speech. Local chat is only heard by people standing near you.

comm-tut-whisper-bubble = Write a whispered message. Start it with a comma, for example: ",quietly testing comms".
comm-tut-whisper-chat = Whispering is only heard very close by. Use it for quiet phrases when you do not need the whole room to hear you.
comm-tut-whisper-tts = Whispering is only heard very close by. Use it for quiet phrases when you do not need the whole room to hear you.

comm-tut-emote-bubble = Write any emote. Start the message with * or %, for example: "*checks the radio".
comm-tut-emote-chat = Emotes describe your character's action, not direct speech. You can write your own text or use known emotes.
comm-tut-emote-tts = Emotes describe your character's action, not direct speech. You can write your own text or use known emotes.

comm-tut-looc-bubble = Write a short question in LOOC. Start the message with _, for example: "_how do I open the PDA?"
comm-tut-looc-chat = LOOC is out-of-character chat near your character. Use it for short mechanics questions when asking IC would not work.
comm-tut-looc-tts = LOOC is out-of-character chat near your character. Use it for short mechanics questions when asking IC would not work.

comm-tut-radio-explain-bubble = Local chat is heard nearby. Radio is heard by people with the right channel in their headset.
comm-tut-radio-explain-chat = If you need to ask for help from people outside the room, use the radio. The common channel is heard by almost the whole station.
comm-tut-radio-explain-tts = If you need to ask for help from people outside the room, use the radio. The common channel is heard by almost the whole station.

comm-tut-common-radio-bubble = Write in the common radio channel. Start the message with ; for example: ";Comms check".
comm-tut-common-radio-chat = Now send a message in the common radio channel. This lets you quickly ask the whole station for help.
comm-tut-common-radio-tts = Now send a message in the common radio channel. This lets you quickly ask the whole station for help.

comm-tut-open-inventory-bubble = Open the inventory with the button on the left panel or [tutkeybind="OpenInventoryMenu"].
comm-tut-open-inventory-chat = The inventory shows equipped items. Right now we need the ears slot with your headset.
comm-tut-open-inventory-tts = The inventory shows equipped items. Right now we need the ears slot with your headset.

comm-tut-radio-ui-bubble = Examine the headset in your ears slot with [tutkeybind="ExamineEntity"]. Its description shows the available radio channels.
comm-tut-radio-ui-chat = Your headset decides which channels you can use. You have an engineering headset: besides common, it gives you engineering.
comm-tut-radio-ui-tts = Your headset decides which channels you can use. You have an engineering headset: besides common, it gives you engineering.

comm-tut-department-radio-bubble = Write in the engineering channel. You can start the message with :e, for example: ":e Need help in maintenance".
comm-tut-department-radio-chat = Departments often handle their tasks in departmental channels. This creates less noise for the whole station.
comm-tut-department-radio-tts = Departments often handle their tasks in departmental channels. This creates less noise for the whole station.

comm-tut-help-request-example-bubble = A good help request is short and clear: where you are, what happened, and what help you need.
comm-tut-help-request-example-chat = Example: "Engineering, maint tunnel near brig, no power, need an engineer". Try to include the place, the problem, and the action needed.
comm-tut-help-request-example-tts = Example: Engineering, maint tunnel near brig, no power, need an engineer. Try to include the place, the problem, and the action needed.

comm-tut-open-messenger-bubble = Open the PDA messenger. Press [tutkeybind="OpenMessenger"] or open the PDA in your ID slot.
comm-tut-open-messenger-chat = Messenger is useful when a message is not urgent or when you need to write to a department group.
comm-tut-open-messenger-tts = Messenger is useful when a message is not urgent or when you need to write to a department group.

comm-tut-messenger-chats-bubble = The chat list is on the left. It contains direct messages, groups, and invitations.
comm-tut-messenger-chats-chat = In messenger, common chat and departments are in the groups tab. Direct chats are for private messages to a specific character.
comm-tut-messenger-chats-tts = In messenger, common chat and departments are in the groups tab. Direct chats are for private messages to a specific character.

comm-tut-messenger-messages-bubble = The selected chat history is on the right. After choosing a chat, the input field and send button appear below.
comm-tut-messenger-messages-chat = First select the chat you need on the left, then write a message in the field below and press the send button.
comm-tut-messenger-messages-tts = First select the chat you need on the left, then write a message in the field below and press the send button.

comm-tut-messenger-group-tab-bubble = Press the group chats tab.
comm-tut-messenger-group-tab-chat = Common messenger chat is in the groups tab. Press it to see the available group chats.
comm-tut-messenger-group-tab-tts = Common messenger chat is in the groups tab. Press it to see the available group chats.

comm-tut-messenger-common-chat-bubble = Select common chat.
comm-tut-messenger-common-chat-chat = Now select common chat in the list on the left. After you select it, the message input field will appear below.
comm-tut-messenger-common-chat-tts = Now select common chat in the list on the left. After you select it, the message input field will appear below.

comm-tut-send-messenger-bubble = Select common chat and send a short message.
comm-tut-send-messenger-chat = Send a short message in common messenger chat. For example: "Comms check".
comm-tut-send-messenger-tts = Send a short message in common messenger chat. For example: comms check.

comm-tut-ask-help-bubble = If you do not understand a mechanic, ask IC. For OOC questions, use LOOC or AHelp depending on the situation.
comm-tut-ask-help-chat = In game, it is better to ask nearby characters or use radio first. If the question is out of character or you need admin help, use LOOC or AHelp.
comm-tut-ask-help-tts = In game, it is better to ask nearby characters or use radio first. If the question is out of character or you need admin help, use LOOC or AHelp.
